{
  "stem": "868.4",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "These certificates were blocked during the war, because obviously no one could go, come out of-- out of Europe.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Now that the war was over, a part of these certificates of immigration were released.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So I decided I would go, although I didn't know yet what had happened to my mother and to my brother in the north and the whereabouts of my father.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But I figured we would all reunite after the-- the-- the-- the war.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I was convinced that my father would survive because, all throughout the war, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] we had known a lot of hardships I didn't speak about, but hard physical labor and situations that were anything but comfortable.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he pulled through all the time.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So my hope was that him being in need of medical attention, at least until the wound was healing, would help him survive.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I went ahead to establish a new family life.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I didn't want-- I wanted to be as far away from Europe as possible, which was in ruins.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The xenophobia of the French still stuck in my blood.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I wanted to start on fresh grounds where Jews would not be dependent anymore upon the whim of other authorities.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I hooked up again with-- Willy also came-- I hooked up again with Ziggy.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Ziggy, you remember, was the kid my age who was with me in the garrison when we carried the straw back and forth.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But he did not want to take the chance of escaping, and he was in the transport [COUGHS], excuse me, he was in the transport that left the next morning with my father, and it's from him that I heard that my father had been gassed.",
      "word_count": 46
    }
  ],
